gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

Praising Hari's virtues daily, my voice will remain forever; 
Stay in the story of Krishna, this ear remains, with hands folded for Hari's sake.

War devguru dan jaano re, Mukyum tan tedhi paramano re;
Jan kartaan hataan keertan re, Tenae jaanaanu tajiyun tan re.

Know the war of devotion, that is beyond measurement, and know My divine state, too, be it beyond comprehension;

In this song, I am singing, and you are listening, knowing and understanding.

Since you want a direct translation without any additional words, here it is:

That day from our house to that extent read, the sacred scripture so profoundly; 
Scripture says what food it is, and thus performed with companions at meal.

Here is the translation:

All householders are in accordance with their own nature, all expenses are borne by everyone; 
When the festival was over, it had become a day of fourteenth then.
